{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-hypsipetes-philippinus", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-hypsipetes-philippinus", "name": "Philippine bulbul", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "bird-philippine-bulbul-43e83738", "name": "Philippine bulbul", "englishName": "Philippine bulbul", "latinName": "Hypsipetes philippinus", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "The Philippine bulbul (Hypsipetes philippinus) is a songbird species in the bulbul family, Pycnonotidae. It is endemic to the Philippines. Its natural habitats are tropical moist lowland forest and tropical moist montane forest. Description and taxonomy The Philippine bulbul was originally described in the genus Turdus and later placed in the genus Ixos. In 2010, it was re-classified to the genus Hypsipetes as it is very closely related to the type species of that genus, the black bulbul. Until 2010, the Mindoro bulbul, Visayan bulbul and Zamboanga bulbul were all considered as subspecies of the Philippine bulbul. The Philippine bulbul differs from the rest with its lighter plummage, smaller bill and different call. Subspecies Three subspecies are currently recognized: Hypsipetes philippinus parkesi - (du Pont, 1980): Found on Burias Hypsipetes philippinus philippinus - (Forster, 1795): Found in northern Philippines Hypsipetes philippinus saturatior - (Hartert, 1916): Found in eastern-central and southern Philippines Behaviour and ecology It is a generalist that feeds on fruit and insects. Fledglings of the Philippine bulbul were recorded on Mindanao in late April, but the breeding season seems to be prolonged as females with ripe ovarian follicles were still found in April and May. Territorial songs are heard at lower altitudes as late as May, while further upslope the birds are silent at that time of year and presumably engaged in breeding activity. The besra has been recorded as a predator of young Philippine bulbuls, and this or other goshawks might also catch adult birds. Habitat and conservation status Its natural habitat is tropical moist lowland forest, forest edge, clearings, and coconut groves up to 2,000 meters above sea level. A common and adaptable bird as long as sufficient forest remains, it is not considered a threatened species by the IUCN. Footnotes References Gregory, Steven M. (2000): Nomenclature of the Hypsipetes Bulbuls (Pycnonotidae). Forktail 16: 164–166. PDF fulltext Moyle, Robert G. & Marks, Ben D. (2006): Phylogenetic relationships of the bulbuls (Aves: Pycnonotidae) based on mitochondrial and nuclear DNA sequence data. Mol. Phylogenet. Evol. 40(3): 687–695. doi:10.1016/j.ympev.2006.04.015 (HTML abstract) Pasquet, Éric; Han, Lian-Xian; Khobkhet, Obhas & Cibois, Alice (2001): Towards a molecular systematics of the genus Criniger, and a preliminary phylogeny of the bulbuls (Aves, Passeriformes, Pycnonotidae). Zoosystema 23(4): 857–863. PDF fulltext Peterson, A. Townsend; Brooks, Thomas; Gamauf, Anita; Gonzalez, Juan Carlos T.; Mallari, Neil Aldrin D.; Dutson, Guy; Bush, Sarah E. & Fernandez, Renato (2008): The Avifauna of Mt. Kitanglad, Bukidnon Province, Mindanao, Philippines. Fieldiana Zool. New Series 114: 1-43. DOI:10.3158/0015-0754(2008)114[1:TAOMKB]2.0.CO;2 PDF fulltext", "shortSummary": "The Philippine bulbul (Hypsipetes philippinus) is a songbird species in the bulbul family, Pycnonotidae. It is endemic to the Philippines.", "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/01/Philippine_bulbul_%28Hypsipetes_philippinus_saturatior%29_Bohol.jpg/960px-Philippine_bulbul_%28Hypsipetes_philippinus_saturatior%29_Bohol.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-hypsipetes", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-hypsipetes-philippinus", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-hypsipetes", "species": "taxonomy-species-hypsipetes-philippinus"}, "expandable": true, "x": -248.2, "y": -685.71, "z": 656.63}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-hypsipetes-philippinus", "name": "Philippine bulbul", "latinName": "Hypsipetes philippinus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Philippine bulbul（Hypsipetes philippinus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Philippine bulbul。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -248.2, "y": -685.71, "z": 667.79}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-hypsipetes", "name": "Hypsipetes", "latinName": "Hypsipetes", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Hypsipetes（Hypsipetes）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联26种鸟类，如Nicobar bulbul、Philippine bulbul、Mindoro bulbul等26种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 26, "x": -411.38, "y": -425.32, "z": -36.43}], "links": [{"key": "bird-philippine-bulbul-43e83738__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-hypsipetes-philippinus", "source": "bird-philippine-bulbul-43e83738", "target": "taxonomy-species-hypsipetes-philippinus", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-hypsipetes-philippinus__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-hypsipetes", "source": "taxonomy-species-hypsipetes-philippinus", "target": "taxonomy-genus-hypsipetes", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Philippine bulbul 属于属 Hypsipetes。"}]}
